Pre-Stage-7 6-Stage Rule Set

Scope:
- finish the last must-fix work before Stage 7
- keep it practical and deploy-focused
- preserve all working flows
- do not add unrelated features
- do not redesign UI broadly
- do not redesign architecture broadly

The 6 stages:
1. RLS parity
2. minimal status transition rules
3. CTA leak cleanup + final role QA
4. finance automation lite audit + plan
5. finance automation lite implementation
6. finance automation lite QA sweep

Hard role model:
- admin / owner = full operational control
- coordinator = scoped operational control only
- reviewer = review-only or review-oriented actions only
- member / freelancer = personal-scope work only

Finance guardrails:
- no payroll
- no tax
- no invoicing
- no real transfer automation
- keep finance automation light, useful, and internal

Execution guardrails:
- one stage at a time
- do not jump ahead
- stop after each stage
- provide a completion report
- keep changes low-risk and reviewable
